reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 26, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Product worked perfectly and was easy to install. All you need is a level, pencil to mark holes. A hammer to tap in the anchors and a drill. I would purchase again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Garden Tool Organizer
reviews.reviewText: Great product gets all rakes, shovels etc out of the way. The racks will hold almost all types of tools. The only issue was with a smaller rake with a thin metal handle that would slide down. Also the racks come in 17” lengths so if you have a wall with wider studs you may need to add some backing to hang them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Decent idea for the price
reviews.reviewText: Bought these to try and organize yard and other misc tools. They are easy enough to mount. But they are a bit flimsy if I'm being honest. Heavy tools like a big shovel or sledge hammer will sometimes pull themselves free and slide down. It's a novel idea and works well enough for what it is.If it were made a little more heavy duty I probably would have given it a 6. Still works well enough for the money.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 27, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Great product to organize my garage!! Great Quality

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 15, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The package came with four pieces. I lined 3 of them up and put a single one further down the garage wall. I wasn’t sure how the hooks would work but they work very well. I hung a sledge hammer, brooms, rakes and other gardening tools. The grip on the hooks hold the tools in place nicely. Overall a great design. Be sure to screw them into a stud and they will stay in place. Really happy with the purchase. Things are much better organized.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Mid to low-end storage with flimsey L-hooks
reviews.reviewText: Summary: Medium grade storage with square hooks that are too small to hold many items securely. The weight-activated J-hooks are ok but not heavy duty. The price was good but I'm replacing with a heavier duty unit that will meet all my needs... not just a subset. The until comes in multiple 17" sections which must be mounted individually. Perhaps flexible but more work to install. Comes with plastic anchors which require larger holes in sheet rock (16ea). This unit is NOT good for hanging larger items like hedge trimmers, leaf blowers, etc.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great organizer for the garage
reviews.reviewText: Easy to install with a lot of holders

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Works, but not the best quality
reviews.reviewText: I love the size of this organizer and it is very useful for hanging multiple tools! Great that you can use it to latch rakes, shovels, or to hang tools directly on the hooks. My only complaint is that the hooks seem a little loose where they connect to the frame, so they can turn and don't seem like they will hold up. Hopefully, with some care we can make this last because it really makes my shed so tidy!

Product seems pretty decent. Only time will tell. I was even able to hang a gas trimmer. Hope it will hold up. To hang things you need to be careful when you remove them from the orange hooks as they can fall. For someHooks close together I use a long stick to lift the hook while I install the hanging tool.

Well made but I did not give it 5 stars as the hooks are easily bent. If you are going to hang items with any weight I would suggest the you don't use the plastic dowels that come with the organizer. I mounted a wooden backing on the wall and then hung the organizers with wood screws to the backing. You can now hang anything on these organizers and they will never come off the wall.
